WEBVTT

00:09.843 --> 00:11.877
We are
going to be together.

00:11.879 --> 00:13.746
Go home, unpack
a few things,

00:13.748 --> 00:16.315
meet me
here tomorrow night.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.417
(knocking)

00:18.785 --> 00:20.919
Clearly there's nothing
I can say.

00:20.921 --> 00:23.489
Yes, there is...

00:23.491 --> 00:24.957
"I'm staying".

00:24.959 --> 00:25.991
Happy birthday.

00:25.993 --> 00:26.825
Happy birthday!

00:26.827 --> 00:29.661
(Buddy)
The last time you two
celebrated a birthday together,

00:29.663 --> 00:31.697
you were three years old.

00:31.699 --> 00:33.565
I think I'm gonna go
with my mom.

00:33.567 --> 00:34.633
That's awesome.

00:34.635 --> 00:37.302
Too bad Elizabeth is stuck
here with her family.

00:37.304 --> 00:40.005
What do you mean?
What do
you think I mean?

00:40.007 --> 00:40.839
Okay, my son's room?

00:40.841 --> 00:43.876
Your husband knows that you
and I are having an affair.

00:43.878 --> 00:46.078
Trust me, Liz, he knows.

00:46.080 --> 00:48.347
And now, so do we.

00:52.085 --> 00:52.918
I saw my mother.

00:52.920 --> 00:55.387
She's waiting for me to
run away with her.

00:55.389 --> 00:56.455
I don't
know what I want.

00:56.457 --> 00:58.557
I'm your dad
and I'll take care of you.

00:58.559 --> 01:01.093
Carter asked me to say
goodbye for her.

01:01.095 --> 01:02.561
Don't underestimate me,
David.

01:02.563 --> 01:05.097
You made that
mistake once before.

01:05.099 --> 01:07.066
You were amazing.

01:07.068 --> 01:08.801
Was I?
Yes.

01:29.722 --> 01:32.391
Lori should be
here in about ten minutes.

01:35.395 --> 01:37.129
Carter?

01:37.131 --> 01:38.730
Carter?

01:38.732 --> 01:39.198
Carter?

01:39.200 --> 01:40.299
Have you seen my
little girl?

01:40.301 --> 01:45.871
She's got a denim vest
and pink hi-top sneakers.

01:45.873 --> 01:47.106
Carter?

01:49.809 --> 01:52.611
Carter?

01:52.613 --> 01:53.712
Mommy?

01:53.714 --> 01:55.614
Oh, Carter.

01:55.616 --> 01:56.081
Oh.

01:56.083 --> 01:57.683
I was looking all over
for you.

01:57.685 --> 02:00.252
I went with
Happy to feed to ducks.

02:00.254 --> 02:01.687
I was so scared.

02:01.689 --> 02:03.122
Mommy thought she
lost you.

02:03.124 --> 02:04.823
You didn't,
I'm right here.

02:04.825 --> 02:07.025
I can never lose you,
ever, ever, ever.

02:07.027 --> 02:09.094
You're the only
thing that matters to me,

02:09.096 --> 02:11.163
the only thing in
the whole world.

02:11.165 --> 02:12.931
You won't lose me.

02:12.933 --> 02:15.100
Promise, pinky swear?

02:15.102 --> 02:16.768
Promise, pinky swear.

02:16.770 --> 02:18.670
Promise,
pinky swear.

02:22.242 --> 02:24.877
You okay?

02:24.879 --> 02:26.378
Oh-- Yeah.

02:26.380 --> 02:30.849
Just remembering
something.

02:30.851 --> 02:32.351
We're a
little early.

02:37.023 --> 02:40.225
Which direction do you think
she's coming from?

02:40.227 --> 02:42.728
No idea.

02:42.730 --> 02:46.198
When you talked to her
last night,

02:46.200 --> 02:48.300
how upset was
she when you told her

02:48.302 --> 02:51.136
I wasn't going
with her?

02:51.138 --> 02:55.340
I'm sure
you can imagine.

02:55.342 --> 02:56.875
Yeah.

02:59.045 --> 03:03.815
She's always said her
biggest fear was losing me.

03:03.817 --> 03:06.685
She must have known that
would be inevitable.

03:09.856 --> 03:13.258
Thank you
for arranging this meeting.

03:13.260 --> 03:16.695
This decision must have been
pretty hard.

03:16.697 --> 03:20.098
I didn't
want you to regret it.

03:20.100 --> 03:22.167
I don't.

03:22.169 --> 03:24.002
I really don't.

03:24.004 --> 03:26.271
Won't this be weird for
you, though?

03:26.273 --> 03:28.273
What, meeting Lori?

03:32.378 --> 03:34.680
Don't worry about me.

03:37.217 --> 03:44.156
♪

03:47.126 --> 03:49.695
What time is it?

03:49.697 --> 03:51.897
It's still 11:30.

03:51.899 --> 03:54.366
About 11:31.

03:54.368 --> 03:56.802
What should we do?

03:56.804 --> 03:59.304
I say we give it another
half-hour.

03:59.306 --> 04:01.006
That's what
you said half an hour ago.

04:01.008 --> 04:01.840
She's a fugitive.

04:01.842 --> 04:06.144
Maybe she thought she's been
spotted and it wasn't safe.

04:06.146 --> 04:07.646
I don't know,
if she wanted to see me,

04:07.648 --> 04:09.248
she would have
found a way.

04:09.250 --> 04:11.617
Is it possible...

04:11.619 --> 04:14.886
she'd rather not
see you than say goodbye?

04:20.026 --> 04:20.759
Yeah.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.194
If I were
in her position,

04:22.196 --> 04:24.263
I like to think I'd be
generous enough

04:24.265 --> 04:27.399
not to put you
through any more pain,

04:27.401 --> 04:29.968
just let you go live
your life.

04:32.872 --> 04:36.208
Yeah, that sounds
like her.

04:36.210 --> 04:38.310
You wanna go do that?

04:46.886 --> 04:48.920
Okay.

04:51.691 --> 04:54.793
♪ I wanna wake up

04:54.795 --> 04:58.063
